(2) HCFA makes a midyear correction to the wage index for an area only if a hospital can show that_

(i) The intermediary or HCFA made an error in tabulating the hospital's data; and 

(ii) The hospital could not have known about the error, or did not have the opportunity to correct the error, before
the beginning of the Federal fiscal year. A midyear correction to the wage index is effective prospectively from the
date the change is made to the wage index. 



